HSE -Specialist
- ,
Gold Career Provider
This employer achieved a Gold Career Provider status based on their record of hiring on Bayt.com.
Date Posted: 2014/05/05 08:10:18
Ref. JB3047379
Job Description
JOB RESPONSIBILITIES
Coordinate with the stake holders and ensure Risk Assessment and Environmental Impact assessment of all activities and facilities in compliance with HSEMS
Evaluate all applicable legal and other requirements, register and communicate to stake holders
Liaise with relevant regulatory authorities to ensure the organization is compliant with applicable legislations
Ensure all incidents are reported, recorded and investigated
Administer and maintain online Incident Reporting System
Develop and implement Emergency management system
Participate in all emergency exercises and follow up with identified actions
Monitor and measure performance of the assigned entities and functions against HSEMS with appropriate reports, analysis, statistics and reviews
Conduct periodical inspections and assessments, communicate the findings, advise suggestions for improvement and ensure findings are translated into action plans
Ensure Procurement and Contractor management in compliance with HSEMS
Develop and implement Permit to Work in compliance with HSEMS
Ensure modification or relocation of People, Property and process are in compliance with HSEMS
Ensure all relevant documents are retained and secured in line with TECOM policies
Impart HSE competencies and awareness to HSMS stake holders as identified
Update HSE competencies through trainings, workshops through research, preparation and organization of educational materials and techniques
Co-ordinate and arrange for HSE training by external training organizations
Skills
Leadership
Ensure compliance with TECOM HSE Policy at assigned Entities and Functions Develop and implement OHSAS 18001 & ISO 14001 Certifiable management system

Establish and review annual objectives and programs in the areas of responsibility
Communicate established Policies and programs to all HSE Management System (HSEMS) stakeholders
Participate in development and implementation of HSEMS in the areas of responsibility
Provide consultation to promote HSEMS among stake holders
Set an example to employees, visitors and contractors by promoting and conforming to the company HSE policies and programs
